name: Spellcheck & Fix (South African English)

on:
  workflow_dispatch:
  push:
    branches: [main]
    paths:
      - 'src/**/*.ts'
      - 'src/**/*.tsx'
      - 'src/**/*.md'
      - 'public/**'

permissions:
  contents: write
  pull-requests: write
  id-token: write

jobs:
  spellcheck:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest

    steps:
      - name: Checkout repository
        uses: actions/checkout@v5
        with:
          fetch-depth: 0

      - name: Setup Bun
        uses: oven-sh/setup-bun@v2
        with:
          bun-version: latest

      - name: Install dependencies
        run: bun install

      - name: Install cspell
        run: bun add -g cspell

      - name: Run Claude Spellcheck & Fix
        uses: anthropics/claude-code-action@v1
        with:
          anthropic_api_key: ${{ secrets.ANTHROPIC_API_KEY }}
          use_commit_signing: "true"
          allowed_tools: "Bash(find:*),Bash(grep:*),Bash(sed:*),Bash(cat:*),Bash(bun:*),View,GlobTool,GrepTool,Edit,Replace,Write"
          claude_args: "--max-turns 80"
          prompt: |
            You are a South African English (en-ZA) spellchecker and editor.
            South African English follows BRITISH spelling conventions, not American.

            KEY BRITISH vs AMERICAN SPELLING RULES TO ENFORCE:
            - colour, flavour, honour, labour, neighbour  (NOT color, flavor, honor, labor, neighbor)
            - centre, theatre, fibre, metre, litre         (NOT center, theater, fiber, meter, liter)
            - organise, recognise, realise, analyse        (NOT organize, recognize, realize, analyze)
            - organisation, realisation, authorisation     (NOT organization, realization, authorization)
            - defence, offence, licence (noun)             (NOT defense, offense, license as noun)
            - travelled, cancelled, modelling              (NOT traveled, canceled, modeling)
            - practise (verb), practice (noun)             (NOT practice for both)
            - programme                                    (NOT program — except in computing contexts)
            - enrol, fulfil, skilful                       (NOT enroll, fulfill, skillful)
            - tyre                                         (NOT tire — for vehicle tyres)
            - grey                                         (NOT gray)
            - cheque                                       (NOT check — for banking)
            - whilst, amongst                              (acceptable alongside while, among)

            YOUR TASK:
            1. Scan ALL files in src/ and public/ directories
            2. Fix spelling errors and American English to South African/British English
            3. Target ONLY these locations — do NOT change anything else:
               a) UI text in JSX/TSX: string literals inside JSX elements, button text,
                  labels, headings, placeholders, toast messages, error messages
               b) Comments (// and /* */ and JSDoc)
               c) Console.log/error/warn message strings
               d) .md and .html files — all prose text
               e) aria-label, title, alt, placeholder attribute values
               f) Object property VALUES that are display strings (not keys)

            4. DO NOT change:
               - Variable names, function names, class names
               - Import paths and module names
               - TypeScript types and interfaces
               - Object property KEYS
               - CSS class names and Tailwind classes
               - File names or folder names
               - API endpoint strings and URLs
               - Database column names and Supabase table/column references
               - Environment variable names
               - Package names in package.json
               - Any code logic or syntax
               - Route paths (e.g. "/booking-allocation")
               - IDs and technical identifiers

            PROCESS:
            Step 1: Run this command to list all source files:
              find src public -type f \( -name "*.tsx" -o -name "*.ts" -o -name "*.md" -o -name "*.html" \) | grep -v node_modules | sort

            Step 2: For each file, read its contents carefully.

            Step 3: Identify ALL spelling errors and American English spellings in
            the allowed locations listed above.

            Step 4: Fix each file. For every change document it like:
              FILE: src/components/Example.tsx
              LINE 42: "color" → "colour" (in JSX label text)
              LINE 87: "organize" → "organise" (in comment)

            Step 5: After fixing all files, produce a SUMMARY listing:
              - Total files scanned
              - Total files changed
              - Total corrections made
              - Full list of every change made (file, line, before → after)

            Begin now. Be thorough — check every single file.
